      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 303,
      "message": "The method being tested has void return type.\nBecause DataOutputStream is a final class we use PowerMockito to mock it and @PrepareForTest on it which works for non-final methods of the class.\nTo do a verify on final methods of this final class is not possible without a @PrepareForTest annotation creating a proxy object for the class under test which would mean we lose the code coverage for the entire class.\nThis is because the Java compiler identifies the real object methods (where they are final) before mocking can substitute the proxy bytecode manipulated version.",
      "author": {
